---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy — Code Cowboys LLC" description="Privacy Policy for Code Cowboys LLC apps and website.">
  <Nav />

  <div class="privacy-wrap">
    <div class="inner privacy-inner">

      <div class="privacy-header">
        <div class="section-label">Legal</div>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <div class="meta">
          <span>Effective Date: May 16, 2026</span>
          <span>Last Updated: May 16, 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-body">

        <div class="summary-box">
          <h2>Summary</h2>
          <p>We've designed our applications with privacy as a core principle. Your health tracking data — including food intake logs, symptom records, and any health information you enter into our apps — is stored only on your device. We do not collect, transmit, or have access to this data. The limited information we do collect is described below.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>Account Information</h3>
        <p>When you create an account, we collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your email address</li>
          <li>A password (stored as a cryptographic hash; we cannot see your actual password)</li>
          <li>Optional: a display name</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Subscription and Payment Information</h3>
        <p>If you purchase a subscription:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Payments are processed by Apple (App Store), Google (Google Play), or Stripe (web subscriptions, when available)</li>
          <li>We receive confirmation of your subscription status and a customer identifier from the payment processor</li>
          <li>We do not receive or store your credit card details, billing address, or other payment information — those are held only by the payment processor</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Technical Information</h3>
        <p>When you use our apps, we may collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Anonymized crash reports to diagnose and fix bugs (no personal data included)</li>
          <li>Basic device information (operating system version, app version, device model)</li>
          <li>Approximate usage statistics (app open frequency, feature usage) — anonymized and not tied to your identity</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can opt out of crash reports and usage statistics in app settings.</p>

        <h3>Information We Do Not Collect</h3>
        <p>We do not collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The food items you log</li>
          <li>Symptom data you record</li>
          <li>Any other health information you enter into our applications</li>
          <li>Your precise location</li>
          <li>Contents of your device beyond what you choose to share with us</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="callout">Your health tracking data is stored only on your device.</div>

        <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide and maintain our services</li>
          <li>Verify your subscription status</li>
          <li>Communicate with you about your account or service changes</li>
          <li>Diagnose technical problems and improve app stability</li>
          <li>Respond to your support requests</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell your information to third parties. We do not use your information for advertising.</p>

        <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Account information is stored on servers operated by Cloudflare</li>
          <li>Data is encrypted in transit (HTTPS/TLS) and at rest</li>
          <li>Access to account data is limited to authorized personnel</li>
          <li>Your on-device data is protected by your device's operating system security</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
        <p>You can:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>View your account information at any time within the app</li>
          <li>Update or correct your email or display name</li>
          <li>Delete your account at any time, which removes your account information from our servers</li>
          <li>Export your on-device data in a portable format (JSON/CSV) via in-app export</li>
          <li>Opt out of crash reporting and analytics in app settings</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To delete your account or request data export, email us at <a href="mailto:privacy@code-cowboys.com">privacy@code-cowboys.com</a>.</p>
        <p>If you are a resident of California, the European Union, the United Kingdom, or another jurisdiction with specific data protection laws, you may have additional rights under those laws. Contact us using the email above for any requests.</p>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>Our applications are not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If you believe we have inadvertently collected such information, please contact us so we can delete it.</p>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>Our applications may use the following third-party services, each governed by their own privacy policies:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Apple App Store / Google Play</strong> — for app distribution and subscription processing</li>
          <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — for web-based subscription processing (when applicable)</li>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — for our website and account servers</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy as our services evolve or legal requirements change. When we make significant changes, we will update the "Last Updated" date and notify users via email or in-app notification. Continued use of our applications after a change indicates acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <div class="contact-block">
          <p><strong>Code Cowboys LLC</strong></p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@code-cowboys.com">privacy@code-cowboys.com</a></p>
          <p>Website: <a href="https://code-cowboys.com">code-cowboys.com</a></p>
          <p>For privacy-related requests (access, deletion, correction), please use the email above and include the email address associated with your account.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .privacy-wrap {
    padding: 60px 0 80px;
  }

  .privacy-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .privacy-header {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
    padding-bottom: 32px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .privacy-header h1 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: #f5ead6;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .meta span {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .privacy-body h2 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f5ead6;
    margin: 44px 0 14px;
    padding-top: 44px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .privacy-body h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; padding-top: 0; border-top: none; }

  .privacy-body h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #d4b87a;
    margin: 28px 0 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 11px;
  }

  .privacy-body p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .privacy-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 16px 0;
    padding-left: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .privacy-body li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .privacy-body li::marker { color: var(--gold); }

  .privacy-body a {
    color: var(--gold);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .privacy-body strong { color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 500; }

  .summary-box {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
    padding: 24px 28px;
    margin-bottom: 44px;
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }

  .summary-box h2 {
    margin: 0 0 12px !important;
    padding: 0 !important;
    border: none !important;
    font-size: 18px !important;
  }

  .summary-box p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .callout {
    background: rgba(201,144,30,0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(201,144,30,0.2);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #8a7254;
    margin: 4px 0 20px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .contact-block {
    background: var(--bg2);
    padding: 24px 28px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .contact-block p { margin: 0; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .privacy-header h1 { font-size: 36px; }
    .privacy-wrap { padding: 40px 0 60px; }
  }
</style>